President Muhammadu Buhari has appointed Thomas M.A. John as Acting Alternate Chairman of the NNPC Governing Board. Dr. John, a former Group Managing Director of the NNPC, is before the appointment, a member of the NNPC Governing Board. Maikanti Baru,the Group Maning Director of NNPC said in a statement late Tuesday that John will hold the position of the Acting Alternate Chairman of the Governing Board until a new Minister of Petroleum Resources or Minister of State for Petroleum Resources is appointed to assume the Chairmanship or Alternate Chairmanship position, respectively in line with Sections 1(3) and 2(1) of the NNPC Act. The new appointment takes effect, immediately,Baru affirmed further.  HARRISON EDEH, ABUJA